<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="missing-adj">missing <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'mɪsɪŋ/    美 /'mɪsɪŋ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>丢失的；失踪的；缺少的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a book with some pages missing 
缺了几页的书</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My gloves have been missing for ages. 
我的手套已经丢了很久了。</p></div>

<p>注: 表示“丢失的”、“失踪的”可用missing或lost。  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The missing boy was finally found. 
失踪的男孩终于找到了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The library charged me a fine for the lost book. 
书丢了，图书馆罚了我款。</p></div>

<p>注: be missing表示状态；get lost表示动作。  </p>
<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Police are now searching for a woman who is reported to <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (miss) since the flood hit the area last Friday.  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. have been missing  </p></div>